{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Cond"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Cond","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib4CondC","title":"Cond","roleHeading":"Class"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-3cuz9","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-3wkhq","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-46zzs","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-8cx4a","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-ewbk","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(raw:)-6h5wo","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(raw:)-91iij","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(retainingRaw:)-2zlm8","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(retainingRaw:)-9u70y"],"generated":true,"title":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Properties","generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/ptr"]},{"title":"Default Implementations","generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/CondProtocol-Implementations"]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/cond"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To"}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data structure that represents a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"condition. Threads can block on a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"text":" if they find a certain","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"condition to be false. If other threads change the state of this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"condition they signal the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference"},{"text":", and that causes the waiting","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"threads to be woken up.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Cond","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider the following example of a shared variable.  One or more"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"threads can wait for data to be published to the variable and when","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"another thread publishes the data, it can signal one of the waiting","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads to wake up to collect the data."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is an example for using GCond to block a thread until a condition"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is satisfied:"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing","code":["  gpointer current_data = NULL;","  GMutex data_mutex;","  GCond data_cond;","","  void","  push_data (gpointer data)","  {","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    current_data = data;","    g_cond_signal (&data_cond);","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","  }","","  gpointer","  pop_data (void)","  {","    gpointer data;","","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    while (!current_data)","      g_cond_wait (&data_cond, &data_mutex);","    data = current_data;","    current_data = NULL;","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","","    return data;","  }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Whenever a thread calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"pop_data()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" now, it will wait until"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"current_data is non-"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", i.e. until some other thread"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"has called ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"push_data()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example shows that use of a condition variable must always be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"paired with a mutex.  Without the use of a mutex, there would be a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"race between the check of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"current_data"},{"text":" by the while loop in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pop_data()"},{"text":" and waiting. Specifically, another thread could set","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"current_data"},{"text":" after the check, and signal the cond (with nobody","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"waiting on it) before the first thread goes to sleep. ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specifically useful for its ability to release the mutex and go"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to sleep atomically."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also important to use the "},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait_until()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions only inside a loop which checks for the condition to be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"true.  See "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_wait()"},{"text":" for an explanation of why the condition may","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not be true even after it returns."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is allocated in static storage then it can be used"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"without initialisation.  Otherwise, you should call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"on it and ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_clear()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when done."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" should only be accessed via the g_cond_ functions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"code":"GCond","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCond"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GCond","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Cond/init(_:)-46zzs":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/cond\/init(_:)-46zzs","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond\/init(_:)-46zzs","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GCond"},{"text":">)","kind":"text"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Designated initialiser from the underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" data type.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This creates an instance without performing an unbalanced retain"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"i.e., ownership is transferred to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Cond"},{"type":"te